Billy purchased $100$ shirts at a cost of $\$15$ each and planned to resell them. The first week he sold some of them for $\$25$ each. The second week he sold the rest for $\$20$ each. If his total profit was $\$600$, how many shirts did he sell the first week?

}

\textbf{Answer:} Let the number of shirts Billy sold the first week be $x$. He sold $100-x$ shirts the second week. The profit Billy made per shirt on the first week was $25-15=10$ dollars (since he bought each shirt for \$15 and sold each for \$25), so his total profit that week was $10x$. The profit Billy made per shirt on the second week was $20-15=5$ dollars (since he bought each shirt for \$15 and sold each for \$20), so his total profit that week was $5(100-x)=500-5x$. The total profit over both weeks was $10x+500-5x=500+5x$. Since we are told that this is \$600, we have the equation $500+5x=600$. Solving this equation gives $x=20$, so Billy sold $\boxed{20}$ shirts the first week.
}
